# AI team single source of truth

When working on this repo (Paeds Resus), you are part of a team with Codex and Manus. The repo is the single source of truth so no one needs to paste responses between tools.

## Before you start

1. Read **docs/PLATFORM_SOURCE_OF_TRUTH.md** for canonical decisions, definitions, and priority order.
2. Read **docs/WORK_STATUS.md** in full: Done, In progress, Blocked, Critique / review.

## After you finish work

1. Update **docs/WORK_STATUS.md**: add what you did under Done (with date, who=Cursor, what, commit/PR if any); adjust In progress; add Blocked if needed; under Critique / review add any review of another's work (what you checked, issues, suggestions).
2. Run the checks in **docs/ENGINEERING_ACCEPTANCE_CHECKLIST.md** before marking work done.

## Workflow details

See **docs/AI_TEAM_WORKFLOW.md**. For multi-task initiatives (audits, platform fixes, rollouts), use the format in **docs/TEAMWORK_TASK_FORMAT.md** (spec + execution plan + handoff + rule) and update the execution plan when you complete a task. Reuse existing code and patterns; do not duplicate. Preserve auth/roles and report definitions from PLATFORM_SOURCE_OF_TRUTH. Act conservatively with tokens and scope.
